<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugreldek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greldek</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/00 8:09:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Class for PVP</span><hr size=1> any class...as long as you know what yer doing.<br>
 <p><font color="red"><I><B>Krygal</B><BR>Barbarian Warrior of Vallon Zek<BR>Shanks<BR> <BR></font></I>
<font color="gray"><I><B>It's to bad that whole families can be torn apart by something as simple as a pack of wolves. </B></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/00 9:29:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Class for PVP</span><hr size=1> From a mid-20's mage i talked to.. he said that mages cant PK very well in their mid-20's and cannot pk in their mid-30's.... not sure if thats true.<br>
<br>
Rogues do fine in PvP with the right gear and the right training<br>
<br>
I worked a 30 necro at level 26 to less than a bub.... then he got a good shadow step off and healed.. so i lost.  If i had any throwing stars on me he would have died while i was at a half bubble. He was very impressed. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A> at: 12/26/00 9:40:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/00 11:29:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Class for PVP</span><hr size=1> I'd say necro, as they can sic their pet on you, dot, darkness, and then just shadow step away.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><font size=-1>
<a href="maileto:chris.painter@juno.com">Canbik the Rogue</a> (25)<br>
<a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/bsilentvigilforums">Silent Vigil</a><br>
<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Ring Warden of Rallos Zek</a><br>
<a href="http://www.tribalwar.com/forums/showthread.php?threadid=24539&pagenumber=1">"All your base are belong to us!"</a> <br></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umilkichocolate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milki Chocolate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/00 12:04:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1>     Eh, Mages suck. Really, if you have half assed MR you could beat a mage in a few seconds. Earth Pet root just about never sticks for any good amount of time after like lvl 12 with maybe 40+ MR. Though the nukes can get pretty nasty. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukanshu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanshu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/00 12:11:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I think the melee classes prevail here, no offense but a decent MR will do wonders for PvP, for instance a warrior can fight, wear plate and if needed can carry all the fundamentals for PvP combat such as SoW potions and pumice stones, a monk on the shorter wnd of the stick when it comes to armor wise but again, great damage output same with rogues, lightly armored tanks (I call them paper tanks). but that's just a view of myself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/godamage/Kanshu2.jpg>
<br>Kanshu - Loyal Swiftail of Tallon-Zek<br><b>You lika my cat suit? ^_^</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uozzes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ozzes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.pacbell.net/dsantos/babykick.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/00 12:13:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/jfoc69/limbo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Class for PVP</span><hr size=1> druids try to kite you, so do rangers.<br>
necros and sks just kill you...<br>
shamans have great dots and debuffs which are a pain<br>
wars have hp...rootn'nukem<br>
pals are the same as wars but can heal<br>
clerics...damn hard to kill. get them low, they heal. get em low, they heal, etc...<br>
rogues...all depends on their equip and skill. they dont circle strafe and try to be a war they die. quick.<br>
monks are tough, mend+good attacks=tough fight.<br>
bards are a pain with their AE songs. <p><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/dsantos/babykick.gif>Man this Tae-Bo workout makes me feel young again!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udetto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Detto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/00 10:33:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Necros</span><hr size=1>  <br>
  If you play on RZ and get raped by gangbangs all the time....make a necro.  Pet one the healer and EB on the caster..then you you can tap till the caster is dead. EB the healer. Both dead as long as they arent near a zone. 54+ Necroes 0wn all no matter what the opponents got.  EB and Deflux 0wnz j00. Pet's quad for 57 and solo casters.  I know my wiz has taken a Nec down but he had the jump. Root pet and DoF the nec to death. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufabatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fabatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/00 7:32:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://users.erols.com/piccolojm/por.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> cleric </span><hr size=1> I play on Tallon (when Im bored) and I use a cleric <br>
that might sound dumb but there dam good..I can kill yellow melees and white and below mages(as long as I can cast on them). He is level 10(I don't plan to level the charter cus I just kill people in west free port)..what I do is blind root and beat them down with my FS moring star. When the humans team up on me I just run and usally they can't find me..I find that the milita house or caster place. The only bad thing about cleric is I can't kill hummans cus I would become kos..So i just knock them down and ask for food and water..and if they don't give it to me or they don't have any I just heal them up a bit and send them on there way..So maybe mages are the best..just wanted to say clerics are decent pkers as long as you know what your doing (and you don't get snared) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanitylost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanity Lost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/29/00 12:25:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Errrrrrrrr...!!</span><hr size=1> *notices Fabatin's personal picture and frantically claws at his eyes*<br>
<br>
NEXUS!!!!!!! YARRRRRRRRRRR!!!<br>
<br>
(back on topic) I'd say there's no real best, but in most cases, I'd Say Wizard, Druid, Rogue, and SK. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umilkichocolate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milki Chocolate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/29/00 4:34:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bah Humbug</span><hr size=1>    Here are my picks, in no special order:<br>
<br>
Druid - Good, but theres alot of stereotyping and kiting can get fricken boring. They can escape stuff easily =P<br>
<br>
Wizard - Spells cast like fricken crazy. And it thats not fast enough they can shadowstep/fade away to be sure to get that spell off. I guess I didn't mention their nukes hurt like hell?<br>
<br>
Necro - Owch. Dots. I can't feel my legs. <br>
<br>
Rogue - Man, these guys just own. If anything they are the most fun. =) They got nifty little tricks for every situation, and pass out the damage like its cookies. No caster will be able to get a spell off with these guys hammering them.<br>
<br>
SK/Monks - I was skepticle bout putting them here... but if there is a skilled owner they are extremly deadly. But not too many people with that kind of skill come across these classes, so thats why good ones are so rare. Hats off to Zeyroh.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukenric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/01 9:16:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> IMO</span><hr size=1> Bards all the way, if a bard doesn't wanna die, you ain't gonna kill em.  Druid kiting?  I say bah humbug to dat, as a bard is about 10x as annoying to PK-kite.  They're just mean, and like I said already...if they don't want you to catch 'em, you won't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kenric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubedrenkenpigsticker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bedrenken Pigsticker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/bedrenken/halfman.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/01 10:34:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/bedrenken/bedrude.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMO</span><hr size=1> Well, bards aren't completely immune to being jumped. They can't escape so easily in dungeon situations.<br>
<br>
Out in the open though, there's no way you're killing a bard that doesn't want to be killed. <p>Bedrenken Pigsticker<Br>
56th level half-man bastard<br>
Povar server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/01 2:38:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMO</span><hr size=1> It took me about five root poisons to realize that bards suck.  They cancel root immediatly by singing their annoying songs.  <br>
<br>
Bards aren't the best at killing people (they're probably one of the worst), but I think they're easily the hardest to kill in the open (especially for a melee).<br>
<br>
SKs tend to be my toughest opponents, followed closely by druids...unless I can cancel their sow, then they're meat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udinadaandedenaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinadaan DeDenaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/01 5:17:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMO</span><hr size=1> 1  to 8  melee   Everyone runs same speed, and you got more hps  and armor and weapon choice.<br>
8  to 16 mage    Earth pet<br>
16 to 24 necro   Darkness and DoTs, poison DD at 24<br>
24 to 34 druid   DoT, DD, Healing, Speed, Travel<br>
34 to 44 shaman  Pet, DoTs, DD, Healing, SoW<br>
44 to 50 wizard  step, big DD<br>
51 plus  wizard, shaman, melee I figure,,,,all depends on resists and situation IMO<br>
<br>
I think overall best at high levels is shaman. SoW, healing, and poison and disease based DoTs (shared by necros now tho). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udinadaandedenaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinadaan DeDenaan</A> at: 1/6/01 5:19:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uitzena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Itzena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/01 6:21:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IMO</span><hr size=1> High levels?<br>
Necro and druid.<br>
<br>
Lower levels?<br>
